SIMPLE: introvert
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Introvert
<hw>In`tro*vert"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Introverted</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Introverting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Pref. <ets>intro-</ets> +
L. <ets>vertere</ets>, <ets>versum</ets>, to turn.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To turn or bend inward.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Introverted</xex> toes.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Cowper.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To look within; to introspect.</def> <rj><au>Lew
Wallace.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Introvert</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Introvert
<hw>In"tro*vert`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
person who is introverted; one concerned predominantly with himself or
his own feelings. Contrasted with <contr>extrovert</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A person who is shy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A part that can be
introverted{1}.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>introverted</ent>⟦br⟧
